Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.03,0:06:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m not your tool!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.08,0:06:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll decide my future myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.14,0:06:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,After that she became a better parent. She never says anything about my choices now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.48,0:06:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry. That was a pretty depressing story.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.23,0:06:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Then she knows about us becoming manga artists?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.78,0:06:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, she knows, and she’s okay with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.39,0:06:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.40,0:07:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing, just glad to hear that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.78,0:07:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re smart, but I thought you just randomly decided to be a manga artist.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.88,0:07:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that’s kind of true.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.82,0:07:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we should probably get going now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.41,0:07:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.45,0:07:21.42,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\bord0\fs14\fnHelveticaNeue LT 65 Medium\c&HDBDADD&\shad1\xshad-1\4c&H545343&\frx348\fry8\frz2.8\move(338,331,402,331,0,2949)}Yueisha
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.31,0:07:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.05,0:07:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I can’t believe we’re bringing in a manuscript while we’re still in middle school.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.34,0:07:26.17,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\bord0\fs25\fnHelveticaNeue LT 65 Medium\c&HFAFFF3&\shad2\xshad-2\4c&H999881&\frz0.219\frx36\fry332\move(264,-4,264,84,21,1814)}Yueisha
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.60,0:07:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone can bring a manuscript in.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.49,0:07:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What matters is how much they like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.05,0:07:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.47,0:07:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And what might be the purpose of your visit today?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.43,0:07:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Um— We wanted to submit a manuscript—
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.65,0:07:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Then please register at the reception desk over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.20,0:07:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Th-Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.11,0:08:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi. How may I help you today?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.59,0:08:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re here to submit a manuscript—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.65,0:08:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have an appointment?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.02,0:08:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, at 3 o’clock with Mr. Hattori from Shonen Jack.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.40,0:08:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Then could you please fill out this form for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.29,0:08:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Th-There are two of us, so do we each fill one out?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.42,0:08:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,No, one form is enough for both of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.34,0:08:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,U-Um, I’m still a student so for ‘Company Name’...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.80,0:08:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, just write the name of your school.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.34,0:08:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m really sorry— I made a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.76,0:08:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You can just fill out a new form.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.66,0:08:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I’m done.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.62,0:08:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.53,0:08:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait just a second, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.28,0:08:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! However long it—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.95,0:08:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,She said it’d be ‘just a second’.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.59,0:08:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the reception desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.86,0:08:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Takagi and Mr. Mashiro are here to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.60,0:08:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.89,0:08:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for your patience!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.92,0:08:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don’t mind waiting in the third cubicle, Mr. Hattori will be with you shortly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.86,0:08:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.55,0:09:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.35,0:09:03.98,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\bord0\c&H4B4D42&\fnHelveticaNeue LT 65 Medium\frx6\fry330\frz11\pos(435,119)}Meeting Corner Hours
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.09,0:09:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So they don’t just let anyone with a manuscript into the editing department.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.98,0:09:04.10,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\bord0\c&H4B4D42&\fnHelveticaNeue LT 65 Medium\frx6\fry330\frz11\pos(435,119)\clip(480,75,559,127)}Meeting Corner Hours
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.35,0:09:04.48,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\bord0\c&H4B4D42&\fnHelveticaNeue LT 65 Medium\frx6\fry330\frz11\pos(435,119)\clip(m 349 75 l 461 81 453 137 349 191)}Meeting Corner Hours
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.48,0:09:04.60,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\bord0\c&H4B4D42&\fnHelveticaNeue LT 65 Medium\frx6\fry330\frz11\pos(435,119)\clip(m 545 76 l 562 73 554 129 537 139)}Meeting Corner Hours
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.73,0:09:04.85,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\bord0\c&H4B4D42&\fnHelveticaNeue LT 65 Medium\frx6\fry330\frz11\pos(435,119)\clip(m 340 129 l 383 119 384 143 344 147)}Meeting Corner Hours
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.85,0:09:04.98,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\bord0\c&H4B4D42&\fnHelveticaNeue LT 65 Medium\frx6\fry330\frz11\pos(435,119)\clip(m 340 129 l 525 82 541 90 534 116 342 156)}Meeting Corner Hours
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.98,0:09:05.73,Signs,,0,0,0,,{\bord0\c&H4B4D42&\fnHelveticaNeue LT 65 Medium\frx6\fry330\frz11\pos(435,119)}Meeting Corner Hours
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.01,0:09:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.62,0:09:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I like your enthusiasm.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.82,0:09:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But you need to make it clearer to the readers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.96,0:09:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.83,0:09:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So I’ll pretend that I never saw this manuscript.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.49,0:09:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.15,0:09:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Put a little more thought into it and try again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.73,0:09:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring in something interesting next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.99,0:09:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Th-Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.18,0:09:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,D-Did you hear that just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.25,0:09:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re here for the same reason we are, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.98,0:09:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.26,0:09:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I was pretty confident up till now,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.18,0:09:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,but I suddenly think he’ll say it’s terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.85,0:09:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It’d be scarier if they {\i1}liked{\i0} the first manuscript we brought in.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.05,0:09:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,My uncle said it’s a good sign if they at least offer us tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.47,0:09:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Takagi and Mashiro?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.35,0:09:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.49,0:09:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m Hattori, an editor for Shonen Jack.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.06,0:09:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.28,0:09:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you too!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.12,0:10:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s not waste time, so can I see the manuscript?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.61,0:10:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.83,0:10:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.58,0:10:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys don’t have to be so nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.04,0:10:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.08,0:10:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,F-Finally...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.49,0:10:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s such a fast reader!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.26,0:10:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me read it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.84,0:10:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.10,0:11:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“The Two Earths.”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.78,0:11:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The Earth we live on is not the Real Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.70,0:11:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All of it is no more than a model for experimentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.61,0:11:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,...created by {\i1}them{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.50,0:11:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Hayato set foot on his home soil for the first time in a while, after being sent back to recover from a war injury.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.24,0:11:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But only a cruel reality awaited him: the death of his lover, Amy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.25,0:11:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.96,0:11:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Get a grip, Hayato! She’s dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.92,0:11:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw her! She was right over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.14,0:11:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.14,0:11:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,My eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.81,0:11:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,When the light enveloping his body disappeared, he was in a place he didn’t recognize.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.80,0:11:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Where am— What hap—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.30,0:11:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.40,0:11:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Please wait, Amy!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.80,0:11:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you running away?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.20,0:12:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome, the Other Hayato.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.22,0:12:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m the other...?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.15,0:12:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean? Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.90,0:12:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re on Earth. Well, the Real Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.64,0:12:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The Earth where you Clones live is a test model for the Real Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.50,0:12:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s where we, the Real Earthlings, simulate various scenarios.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.80,0:12:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.84,0:12:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In getting closer to the truth, Hayato became captive.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.23,0:12:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,A resistance group known as “Missing” saved him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.54,0:12:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You too?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.92,0:12:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we’re from the Other Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.79,0:12:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,They capture us Clones when they want to send Investigators in.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.16,0:12:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Then when the Investigators are done, they wipe our memories and send us back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.21,0:13:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But if the Investigators are killed, we have no way back, so we have to live here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.69,0:13:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Here in this shitty utopia.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.45,0:13:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s your way back!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.51,0:13:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Hayato returned to Earth and told his people the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.12,0:13:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to make them see: we’re not just dolls for them to play with!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.45,0:13:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, the Other Earth began its counterattack.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.98,0:13:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey now. You really think you can shoot me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.66,0:13:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m your Original, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.87,0:13:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re not just your guinea pigs!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.22,0:13:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Die!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.71,0:13:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys really are... just animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.38,0:13:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The Real Earthlings surrendered.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.42,0:13:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But after years of observation, they had come to a conclusion:
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.84,0:13:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That the Other Earthlings were merely foolish barbarians.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.14,0:14:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy, it’s over...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.52,0:14:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s all over...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.25,0:14:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But you’re no longer here...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.02,0:14:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I won’t forgive you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.95,0:14:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m your Amy!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.35,0:14:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The dead Amy was an Investigator!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.08,0:14:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If an Investigator dies, the Clone can’t come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.68,0:14:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But you showed yourself to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.44,0:14:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Original let me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.45,0:14:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a kind man.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.51,0:14:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But the one I loved was always you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.71,0:14:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve missed you so much, Hayato!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.10,0:14:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,As he felt his love close to him, Hayato rethought his hate.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.43,0:14:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Real and Fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.24,0:14:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Real Earth and the Other Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.39,0:14:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Which one was the actual reality?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.90,0:14:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,This is very well-done.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.66,0:15:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m gonna have some coffee. Would you two like anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.74,0:15:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,W-We’ll have coffee too, please. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.88,0:15:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.62,0:15:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, did you two come up with the story together?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.35,0:15:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,N-No. I did the story and Mashiro did the illustrations, completely separate.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.35,0:15:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.81,0:15:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you two hoping to go pro immediately?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.44,0:15:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! As quickly as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.44,0:15:28.19,Q_Q,,0,0,0,,Just “Yes” would’ve been enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.77,0:15:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay then, I’ll start with feedback on the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.93,0:15:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.84,0:15:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,In general, you have a pretty good sci-fi story.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.73,0:15:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I think there are definitely people who’d enjoy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.02,0:15:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.30,0:15:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But I think it’s more suited to be a novel than a manga.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.55,0:15:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s excess narration, and a lot of explanation in the dialogue.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.42,0:15:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don’t use the characters and illustrations to tell the story, making it a manga is pointless.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.43,0:15:59.90,Q_Q,,0,0,0,,We agreed that I wouldn’t say a word about the story,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.90,0:16:01.93,Q_Q,,0,0,0,,but I kind of thought that as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.70,0:16:05.90,Q_Q,,0,0,0,,Of course, an editor would say as much though.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.42,0:16:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The story really is well-done though.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.71,0:16:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But it really seems more suited to be a light novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.82,0:16:13.11,Q_Q,,0,0,0,,There are all kinds of editors.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.28,0:16:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I really want to write manga.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.39,0:16:16.70,Q_Q,,0,0,0,,Is Mr. Hattori someone we can trust?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.79,0:16:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.62,0:16:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And you’re Mashiro, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.33,0:16:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.48,0:16:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I think your art is incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.40,0:16:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.84,0:16:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But while they’re incredible works of art, they’re not manga illustrations.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.88,0:16:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Your lines are too thick.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.53,0:16:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s not enough differentiation between characters and background.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.46,0:16:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to practice more and form your own style.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.81,0:16:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.47,0:16:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.89,0:16:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Mashiro’s only been using the pen two months.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.90,0:16:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Only two months? Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.93,0:16:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.65,0:16:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,If that’s true, I can’t wait to see what he produces in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.37,0:16:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you two like this kind of story?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.98,0:17:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Jack never has this kind of story.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.12,0:17:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought it’d stand out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.94,0:17:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Takagi, you’re the type who figures out what’s popular and what’ll sell before writing, aren’t you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.46,0:17:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just the conclusion I’ve come to,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.45,0:17:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,but in general, there’s two main types of successful manga artists.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.46,0:17:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,There are those who just write whatever they want and it becomes a hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.27,0:17:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people call them geniuses. Others just call them naïve.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.35,0:17:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there are those like you, who calculate how best to create a hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.90,0:17:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But overwhelmingly, it’s not the calculating ones who make it big.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.65,0:17:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,W-Well, maybe that was a little harsh.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.49,0:17:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s more appropriate to say the calculating ones have more hurdles to overcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.78,0:17:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Conversely, the calculating ones who make it, are tough.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.81,0:17:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,They don’t fizzle after one series, which is great for us editors.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.97,0:18:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course I can’t force you, but I hope you’ll bring your next manuscript to us, not another publisher.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.97,0:18:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If I could, I’d like to keep seeing your future works.
